
 ğŸŸ¢ 1. Classes and Objects

 ğŸ§  Real-life analogy

Think of Car blueprint.

* Blueprint â†’ Class
* Real car â†’ Object

Blueprint has design but not real.
Car is real and usable.

Same in Java:

* Class â†’ template
* Object â†’ real instance

---

 ğŸ§¾ Class syntax

```java
class Student {
    String name;
    int age;

    void display() {
        System.out.println(name + " " + age);
    }
}
```

ğŸ‘‰ Class contains:

* Variables (data)
* Methods (behavior)

---

 ğŸ§¾ Creating object

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Student s1 = new Student(); // object creation

        s1.name = "Uday";
        s1.age = 25;

        s1.display();
    }
}
```

 ğŸ”¥ Output

```
Uday 25
```

