 ğŸŸ¢ 2. Packages

 ğŸ§  Real-life analogy

Mobile apps folder:

* WhatsApp folder
* Photos folder
* Music folder

Same â†’ Java packages organize classes.

---

 ğŸ§¾ Creating package

```java
package com.company.student;

public class Student {
    public void show() {
        System.out.println("Inside package");
    }
}
```

---

 ğŸ§¾ Using package

```java
import com.company.student.Student;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Student s = new Student();
        s.show();
    }
}
```

---

 ğŸ¯ Why packages?

âœ” Avoid class name conflict
âœ” Organize project
âœ” Industry standard

---

 ğŸŸ¢ 3. Access Specifiers (VERY IMPORTANT ğŸ”¥)

Controls visibility.

| Access    | Same class | Same package | Other package       |
| --------- | ---------- | ------------ | ------------------- |
| private   | âœ…          | âŒ            | âŒ                   |
| default   | âœ…          | âœ…            | âŒ                   |
| protected | âœ…          | âœ…            | âœ… (via inheritance) |
| public    | âœ…          | âœ…            | âœ…                   |

---

 ğŸ§¾ Example

```java
class Test {

    private int a = 10;
    int b = 20; // default
    protected int c = 30;
    public int d = 40;

    void show(){
        System.out.println(a);
    }
}
```

