 ğŸŸ¢ 4. Constructors

Constructor runs automatically when object created.

 ğŸ§  Real-life analogy

When baby born â†’ name given automatically
Same â†’ constructor initializes object.

---

 ğŸ”¹ Default constructor

```java
class Student {

    Student() {
        System.out.println("Default constructor called");
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Student s = new Student();
    }
}
```

Output:

```
Default constructor called
```

---

 ğŸ”¹ Parameterized constructor

```java
class Student {
    String name;
    int age;

    Student(String n, int a) {
        name = n;
        age = a;
    }

    void display(){
        System.out.println(name + " " + age);
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Student s = new Student("Uday", 25);
        s.display();
    }
}
```

Output:

```
Uday 25
```

---

 ğŸŸ¢ 5. `this` keyword

`this` refers to current object

 ğŸ§  Why needed?

When local variable and instance variable same name.

---

 ğŸ§¾ Example

```java
class Student {
    String name;
    int age;

    Student(String name, int age){
        this.name = name;
        this.age = age;
    }

    void display(){
        System.out.println(name + " " + age);
    }
}
```

 ğŸ”¥ this.name â†’ class variable

 name â†’ constructor variable

---

 ğŸ§¾ Calling method using this

```java
class Test {
    void show(){
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }

    void display(){
        this.show();
    }
}
```

---

 ğŸŸ¢ 6. static keyword

 ğŸ§  Real-life analogy

College name same for all students.

Each student different
But college name same.

So make it static.

---

 ğŸ”¹ Static variable (shared)

```java
class Student {
    String name;
    static String college = "ABC College";

    void display(){
        System.out.println(name + " " + college);
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Student s1 = new Student();
        s1.name = "Uday";

        Student s2 = new Student();
        s2.name = "Ravi";

        s1.display();
        s2.display();
    }
}
```

Output:

```
Uday ABC College
Ravi ABC College
```

---

 ğŸ”¹ Static method

```java
class Demo {
    static void show(){
        System.out.println("Static method");
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Demo.show(); // no object needed
    }
}
```

---

Output:

```
Static block executed
Main method
```

