 ğŸŸ¢ 7. Best Practices (INTERVIEW LEVEL â­)

 ğŸ”¥ Naming conventions

Class â†’ PascalCase

```
StudentData
EmployeeDetails
```

Variable â†’ camelCase

```
studentName
empSalary
```

---

 ğŸ”¥ Always use constructor for initialization

âŒ Bad:

```java
Student s = new Student();
s.name = "Uday";
```

âœ” Good:

```java
Student s = new Student("Uday",25);
```

---

 ğŸ”¥ Make variables private (encapsulation)

```java
class Student {
    private String name;

    public void setName(String name){
        this.name = name;
    }

    public String getName(){
        return name;
    }
}
```

---

 ğŸ”¥ Use static only when needed

Use static for:

* common data
* utility methods
* constants

---

 ğŸŸ£ Interview Questions They Ask ğŸ˜ˆ

 Q1: Difference class vs object?

Class â†’ blueprint
Object â†’ instance

 Q2: Constructor return type?

âŒ No return type

 Q3: Can constructor be private?

âœ” Yes (Singleton)

 Q4: Static belongs to?

Class, not object

 Q5: this keyword refers to?

Current object

